Johnny Edward Nigerian manager Ndubuisi Egbo has guided FK Tirana into the final of the Albania Cup, Saturday PUNCH reports. Tirana overcame a 2-1 first-leg deficit against KF Bylis Ballsh to win  2-0 in the second leg to advance to the final with a 3-2 aggregate win. First-half goals from Ernest Muci and Erjon Hoxhallari secured the aggregate win for the home side, who lost the first fixture 2-1. Tirana will face KS Teuta Durres in the final billed for August 1. Durres defeated Kukesi 2-1 on aggregate in the other semi-final. Meanwhile, Tirana are two wins away from the Albanian league title. Ex-Super Eagles goalkeeper Egbo’s team lead the Albanian Superliga with 66 points from 33 games, four ahead of second-place Kukesi with 62 points from the same games played. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com